# DRY Principles — Web

## Extract, Don't Copy

- If the same logic appears in 2+ places, extract it into a utility, hook, or component
- Shared validation schemas live in `src/schemas/`
- Shared types in `src/types/api/` (generated from OpenAPI) and `src/types/client/` (client-only)
- Shared utilities in `src/lib/`

## Custom Hooks

- Extract reusable stateful logic into hooks: `src/hooks/use[Feature].ts`
- Hooks that wrap RTK Query with extra logic (error handling, transforms) belong here
- Name convention: `useAuth`, `useChessGame`, `useOnboarding`

## Component Reuse

- Before creating a new component, check if an existing atom/molecule can be composed
- Extract repeated layout patterns into templates
- Use composition (children, render props) over creating near-identical components with slight differences

## Do NOT Over-Abstract

- If something is used only once, inline it — premature abstraction is worse than duplication
- A helper function used in one file can stay in that file until it is needed elsewhere
- Do not create "utils" files with 20 unrelated functions — group by domain
